article.headline: Lamar scores 29 to lead Florida A&M over Alabama A&M 76-58
article.description: — Keith Lamar sank six 3-pointers and scored 29 as Florida A&M cruised to a 76-58 victory over Alabama A&M on Monday night.
article.linkText: Lamar scores 29 to lead Florida A&M over Alabama A&M 76-58
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- — Keith Lamar sank six 3-pointers and scored 29 as Florida A&M cruised to a 76-58 victory over Alabama A&M on Monday night. Lamar shot 11 for 14 from the floor, including 6 for 8 from 3-point range for the Rattlers (6-20, 4-11 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Shannon Grant added 12 points and nine rebounds, while Jordan Chatman hit all eight of his free throws and scored 10. Anthony Bryant and Omari Peek-Green both scored nine to lead the Bulldogs (8-20, 7-8). ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
